{{! prompts/shelf_scan.mustache — bookshelf spine extraction prompt }}
Look at this bookshelf photo and list the books you can see. For each book, note the title and author from its spine.

Return your answer as JSON in this format:
{
  "books": [
    {"title": "...", "author": "...", "spine_position": 1, "confidence": "high"}
  ]
}

confidence: "high" if title clear, "medium" if partial, "low" if hard to read.

spine_position: 1-based integer in reading order (top shelf left-to-right, then next shelf down).

author: leave as empty string if not visible on the spine.

Be thorough — include every book whose spine has any readable text. The shelf clearly contains many books. Skip non-book objects like paintings, photo frames, and plants.

Respond with ONLY the JSON object, no surrounding prose or markdown fences.

The photo above is a real bookshelf with many books visible — your output must include those books, not an empty array.
